c Abhishek Sharma b Nitish Reddy

videos.headline: Nitish Reddy to Jitesh Sharma, out Caught by Abhishek Sharma!! Nitish Reddy has the last laugh! 115.8kph, off-cutter into the pitch, Jitesh Sharma walks across to hook. Goes too hard and loses his shape as the ball comes slower than he expects. More height than distance. Abhishek Sharma runs forward and to his left to take a good tumbling catch. Jitesh Sharma c Abhishek Sharma b Nitish Reddy 19(11) [4s-1 6s-1]

Unadkat to Raza, out Caught by Klaasen!! A wicket immediately after the timeout! 130.7kph, on a length from round the wicket, Raza walks across and gets low to try and scoop it to fine leg. He's early into his shot and ends up spooning it to the keeper who doesn't err. Punjab have now lost half their side. Raza c Klaasen b Unadkat 28(22) [4s-2 6s-2]

T Natarajan to Sam Curran, out Caught by Cummins!! Cummins takes an amazing catch and Curran is gone! 134.3kph, short of length ball, Curran stays in his crease to try and slap it over mid-off. It's the hard length from Natarajan and it results in a miscue. Cummins moves back from mid-on and times his jump perfectly at mid-off to take a superb two-handed overhead catch. Natarajan comes back to break the partnership. Sam Curran c Cummins b T Natarajan 29(22) [4s-2 6s-2]

Bhuvneshwar to Dhawan, out Stumped!! Brilliant glovework by Klaasen. The move to bring him up to the stumps works for SRH. Bhuvi has his second and Punjab are in trouble. Dhawan decides to step out and drive, but this good length ball was angled across and it beats the outside edge, Klaasen gloves it cleanly and lights up the stumps in a flash. Dhawan st Klaasen b Bhuvneshwar 14(16) [4s-2]

Bhuvneshwar to Prabhsimran, out Caught by Nitish Reddy!! This was just a matter of time. Prabhsimran never looked at ease and was charging down every ball. Finally holes out to a good catch running back. Fullish delivery outside off, Prabhsimran charges out and throws his bat on the big shot, slices it over the cover-point region and Nitish runs back, keeps his eyes on the ball and takes it with both hands. Prabhsimran c Nitish Reddy b Bhuvneshwar 4(6) [4s-1]

Cummins to Bairstow, out Bowled!! Cleaned up! Bairstow's poor run with the bat continues.. Cummins wins the match-up. He had the wood over Bairstow and it remains that way. SRH have an early wicket. Good length ball and Bairstow has an ugly swipe across the line, misses and the ball hits the top of off-stump. Bairstow b Cummins 0(3)

Sam Curran to Bhuvneshwar, out Caught by Bairstow!! Bhuvneshwar perishes for the team's cause. Full pitcher and it was in the slot, but Bhuvneshwar does not get hold of the loft and mistimes it to long-off, Bairstow runs in and takes a good catch. Bhuvneshwar c Bairstow b Sam Curran 6(8)

Rabada to Cummins, out Bowled!! Cleaned up! Finally Rabada has his name in the wickets column. He's bowled well today without anything to show, now he cleans up the SRH skipper. Good length delivery and Cummins swings across the line, misses and the ball hits the top of middle-stump. SRH have lost their way completely in the last couple of overs. Will they be bowled out? Cummins b Rabada 3(4)

Arshdeep Singh to Nitish Reddy, out Caught by Rabada!! Arshdeep has turned the game on its head. Second wicket in the over and this is the big one of a well-set Reddy. Not a wicket-taking delivery and Reddy would be kicking himself. Full toss at a hittable height and Reddy throws his bat on the big shot, miscues it high and Rabada accepts the catch near long-off. Dhawan has a big smile on his face and the Punjab flags are waving across Mullanpur. Nitish Reddy c Rabada b Arshdeep Singh 64(37) [4s-4 6s-5]

Arshdeep Singh to Abdul Samad, out Caught by Harshal Patel!! It is Arshdeep's night. Third wicket for him and more importantly he breaks the partnership. Samad struck it well but picked out the fielder. Full delivery outside off, Samad slices the loft and hits it straight to deep backward point, Harshal came in a few steps to take the catch. Punjab needed that.. Abdul Samad c Harshal Patel b Arshdeep Singh 25(12) [4s-5]

Arshdeep Singh to Abdul Samad, out Caught by Harshal Patel!! It is Arshdeep's night. Third wicket for him and more importantly he breaks the partnership. Samad struck it well but picked out the fielder. Full delivery outside off, Samad slices the loft and hits it straight to deep backward point, Harshal came in a few steps to take the catch. Punjab needed that.. Abdul Samad c Harshal Patel b Arshdeep Singh 25(12) [4s-5]

Harshal Patel to Klaasen, out Caught by Sam Curran!! Klaasen turned around and started to walk as soon as he hit that. Curran takes the catch, turns towards the crowd and does a double fist pump. This is a massive wicket for Punjab Kings. Even Harshal is delighted. This was a 134.2ks good length delivery and Klaasen looks to loft through the line, gets it high on the bat and miscues it to long-off, Curran makes no mistake. Klaasen c Sam Curran b Harshal Patel 9(9) [4s-1]

Harshal Patel to Tripathi, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! An appeal for caught behind, Jitesh Sharma wasn't so sure this time, but the bowler was confident, so was Sam Curran, he must have heard something because Dhawan has reviewed. Was a slower short ball and Tripathi was looking to ramp it over the keeper's head, the ball has caught the toe-end though and PBKS have another successful review - Tripathi is OUT. A wicket out of nowhere, an innocous slower bouncer and the right-hander only managed to toe-end it on its way to the keeper. Tripathi c Jitesh Sharma b Harshal Patel 11(14) [4s-1]

Sam Curran to Abhishek Sharma, out Caught by Shashank Singh!! Curran has his man and PBKS have got three inside the batting PP> Kept it short and kept it wide as Abhishek came charging down the wicket, he had to reach out on the drive and it came off the lower half - the ball was dying in front of him at cover-point, but Shahshank dived forward, gets both hands under and holds onto a fine catch. Abhishek Sharma c Shashank Singh b Sam Curran 16(11) [4s-2 6s-1]

Arshdeep Singh to Markram, out Caught by Jitesh Sharma!! One brings two for Arshdeep and Punjab have been on the ball tonight. On a good length and shaping across the right-hander, Markram's feet hardly moved as he shaped for the drive, gets a thin edge and Jitesh Sharma does the rest. A blob for Markram and SRH find themselves in a spot of bother. Markram c Jitesh Sharma b Arshdeep Singh 0(2)

Arshdeep Singh to Head, out Caught by Dhawan!! A good running catch and Dhawan does the thigh-slap celebrations after holding onto the catch. On a good length and angling across the left-hander, Head went hard on the drive, lost his poise and skewed it high in the air - it went over mid-off, but so did Dhawan as he ran back, kept his eyes on the ball all the time and completes a fine running catch. Head looked very scratchy and PBKS have removed him pretty cheaply. Head c Dhawan b Arshdeep Singh 21(15) [4s-4]
